When Hubble, Edwin Hubble in 1926 realized
that the nebulae, or some of

00:27:51.989 --> 00:27:55.299
the nebulae, were actually island universes,
he called them, galaxies

00:27:55.299 --> 00:27:58.619
outside the Milky Way.
People started racing around trying to measure

00:27:58.619 --> 00:27:59.619
the distances to these
things.

00:27:59.619 --> 00:28:04.529
And it was clear that we had the universe
wrong, in terms of its size

00:28:04.529 --> 00:28:07.269
by seven orders of magnitude, which is a big
leap.

00:28:07.269 --> 00:28:11.320
There hadn't been a leap that big since -- since
the old earth going round

00:28:11.320 --> 00:28:16.820
the sun business in the 15th century.
Um, the universe may be even bigger than that.

00:28:16.820 --> 00:28:22.549
This, of course, is Schrödinger's cat -- actually,
it looks more like

00:28:22.549 --> 00:28:23.789
sort of Schrödinger's cat turning into Schrödinger's
dog.

00:28:23.789 --> 00:28:28.859
I'm sure you'll all aware of the quantum paradoxes.
What happens to a -- in a quantum dictated

00:28:28.859 --> 00:28:32.299
event?
Do you end up with two of the objects acting

00:28:32.299 --> 00:28:35.059
 -- behaving -- existing
simultaneously?

00:28:35.059 --> 00:28:36.779
The cat that walks out is it the original
cat?

00:28:36.779 --> 00:28:39.119
So on and so forth.
And all this, together with some other fun

00:28:39.119 --> 00:28:43.299
stuff, has led to the idea
of the many worlds hypothesis, which has become

00:28:43.299 --> 00:28:46.080
respectable to
cosmology now.

00:28:46.080 --> 00:28:50.820
There are actually four levels of multi-verse
which cosmologists talk

00:28:50.820 --> 00:28:54.080
about.
One, this level one, that I like to think

00:28:54.080 --> 00:28:58.609
of as the kind of brute force
multi-verse which is simply the universe we

00:28:58.609 --> 00:29:04.099
see is just a tiny part of
a massively, almost infinitely, inflated super-cosmos.

00:29:04.099 --> 00:29:11.690
Same laws of physics everywhere.
Infinite space.

00:29:11.690 --> 00:29:16.460
This means actually that if this holds, which
eminent astronomers,

00:29:16.460 --> 00:29:21.440
cosmologists think it does, the mass of inflation
seems to suggest that

00:29:21.440 --> 00:29:24.599
this is inevitable, that 10 to the 10 to -- I
think it's 10 to the 10

00:29:24.599 --> 00:29:28.330
to the 120 light years away, there is an identical
room to this with an

00:29:28.330 --> 00:29:31.070
identical me and an identical you all sitting
here, being given this

00:29:31.070 --> 00:29:36.509
talk with maybe one word differently.
Level two is the Stanford sort of multi-verse.

00:29:36.509 --> 00:29:40.849
Andrei Linde, who a Russian emigree cosmologist,
very clever chap.

00:29:40.849 --> 00:29:44.779
He's come up with this idea of post-inflationary
bubbles, little

00:29:44.779 --> 00:29:49.460
daughter universes splitting off from ours,
maybe black holes.

00:29:49.460 --> 00:29:53.679
Level three, the many worlds of quantum physics.
Every time you have a quantum event, you have

00:29:53.679 --> 00:29:56.669
a whole new universe, one
where Hitler won World War II, one where there

00:29:56.669 --> 00:29:58.349
was no World War II at
all.

00:29:58.349 --> 00:30:01.830
And level four, which I think is perhaps the
most interesting one,

00:30:01.830 --> 00:30:08.080
which is whole different conceptual universes.
Things like, I'm sure you've all heard of

00:30:08.080 --> 00:30:12.540
the matrix universe, the idea
that the world we see around us might be a

00:30:12.540 --> 00:30:18.700
simulation.
People maybe not a hundred meters from here

00:30:18.700 --> 00:30:23.339
are working with some very
powerful computers, and the big question is,

00:30:23.339 --> 00:30:25.739
is it possible to simulate
consciousness, for example, in a computer?

00:30:25.739 --> 00:30:28.700
If it is, then we shall do it fairly soon,
probably.

00:30:28.700 --> 00:30:31.019
And we shall do it more than once.
We shall do it millions of times probably

00:30:31.019 --> 00:30:34.710
billions of times.
And we simulate the weather, when we run weather

00:30:34.710 --> 00:30:38.399
forecasts.
If you go NOAA or to the UK Met office, they

00:30:38.399 --> 00:30:43.200
run simulations of 10 to
the 9, 10 to the 15 simulations sometimes,

00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:46.460
over days.
And if it's possible to simulate even a smart

00:30:46.460 --> 00:30:49.859
part of the universe, you
don't need to do the whole thing, in a machine

00:30:49.859 --> 00:30:52.710
including consciousness,
and you do this trillions of times over, the

00:30:52.710 --> 00:30:56.110
chances are that we are
living in one of these simulations, so say

00:30:56.110 --> 00:30:59.999
some people, which is weird
and disturbing.

00:30:59.999 --> 00:31:04.209
When faced with arguments like this, some
people click their head in

00:31:04.209 --> 00:31:07.129
the sand.
There was a lecture, famous lecture given

00:31:07.129 --> 00:31:11.239
by Carl Sagan once.
And he was talking about cosmology and weird

00:31:11.239 --> 00:31:15.440
things, and a lady put her
hand up at the end of the talk and said, that,

00:31:15.440 --> 00:31:17.700
it's just the earth.
You're completely wrong, Dr. Sagan, the earth

00:31:17.700 --> 00:31:20.210
doesn't float around in
space.

00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:24.599
It sits on the back of a turtle.
He said, well, you know, what does a turtle

00:31:24.599 --> 00:31:27.950
